In [[English history]], '''Conformists''' were those whose [[Religion|religious practices]] conformed with the requirements of the [[Act of Uniformity]] and so were in concert with the [[Established Church]], the [[Church of England]], as opposed to those of [[nonconformism|Nonconformists]] whose practices were not acceptable to the Church of England.

In a more general (small "c") sense, ''conformists'' are those who attempt to comply with all [[Norm|societal norms]], generally so as to not stand out in any way and hence be subject to potential ridicule or other [[Social control|social sanctions]].

Many people have heard the "Emo Kid" song and belive non-conformism to be an Emo practice. This is in fact false, it actually means going against the ways of the Majority and in no way what so ever is related to the Emo movement (Eastwardly on sunny days, north westardly when the weather isn't particularly great. Although, the movement has been know to randomly shift in direction occasionally, like, for instance, when they all started just heading south for apparently no reason at all.)

A great band that was previously named "Conformist Nation" recently changed their name to to "Awaiting November" due to the lack of being a good name.

